	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84649><span id=Scholar>Troodon</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>709 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.38]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Wrong on two counts:<br><br>First, the idols don't use essenses, they use imbued gems (possibly you're mistaking these for the spiritstones and faithstones, they use essenses, not these.)<br><br>Second, essenses don't use blessed dust.&nbsp;&nbsp;Only known use for blessed dust (of Karana or Tunare, no other deities have blessed dust at this time) is for recipes invlolvced in the POTC (suxh as the mistletoe cutting sickle and the lucky cabbage).  If you mean the celestia essence (which this DOES use), it is created by combining a celestial solvent and a spell component (that makes a 44+ spell, usually) in a mortar and pestle (no fail combine, need not be a rogue).  Celestial essense has nothing to do with blessed dust (in fact, you need the celestial essence TO MAKE blessed dust).<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Nov 21 23:10:20 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Troodon, AKA Zararazu Twoflower, Level 66 Iksar Monk, Solusek Ro<br><br>My profile: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91426</a></td></tr>
